  <content>
    <section>
      <title>Bicycle Pre-Ride Check Procedure</title>
      <paragraph>This document outlines the pre-ride check procedure for bicycles, covering key areas to ensure safety and optimal performance.</paragraph>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>1. Brakes</title>
      <list>
        <item>Check Pads: Ensure brake pads have sufficient material.</item>
        <item>Lever Action: Verify smooth and firm lever action.</item>
      </list>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>2. Tires</title>
      <list>
        <item>Inflation: Check tire pressure. Recommended ranges:</item>
        <list>
          <item>On Road: 55-60 psi</item>
          <item>Off Road: 35-40 psi</item>
        </list>
        <item>Condition: Inspect tires for cracks, splits, or embedded objects.</item>
      </list>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>3. Wheels</title>
      <list>
        <item>Bearings: Check for loose bearings.</item>
        <item>Trueness: Ensure wheels are true (not wobbling).</item>
        <item>Spokes: Verify spokes are not broken and are tight.</item>
        <item>Axle Nuts: Ensure axle nuts are tight.</item>
      </list>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>4. Headset</title>
      <list>
        <item>Tightness: Check for headset bearing tightness. Ensure smooth steering operation.</item>
      </list>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>5. Chain</title>
      <list>
        <item>Movement: Verify easy movement of chain links.</item>
      </list>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>6. Handlebar and Stem</title>
      <list>
        <item>Stem Condition: *Warning: Do not ride with a cracked stem.*
          <list>
            <item>If stem is cracked: Replace stem.</item>
            <item>If stem is loose: Tighten stem.</item>
          </list>
        </item>
        <item>Clamp Bolt: If handlebars twist in stem: Tighten clamp bolt.</item>
      </list>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>7. Computer (if equipped)</title>
      <list>
        <item>Display Readings: Verify the computer displays appropriate readings. Example readings (may vary by model):</item>
        <table>
          <header>
            <cell> </cell>
            <cell> </cell>
          </header>
          <row>
            <cell>Altitude</cell>
            <cell>0 miles</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
